{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I don't know about you, but I haven't quite figured out"},{"time":4000,"text":"exactly what technology means in my life."},{"time":7000,"text":"I've spent the past year thinking about what it really should be about."},{"time":14000,"text":"Should I be pro-technology? Should I embrace it full arms?"},{"time":17000,"text":"Should I be wary? Like you, I'm very tempted by the latest thing."},{"time":22000,"text":"But at the other hand, a couple of years ago"},{"time":24000,"text":"I gave up all of my possessions,"},{"time":27000,"text":"sold all my technology -- except for a bicycle --"},{"time":29000,"text":"and rode across 3,000 miles on the U.S. back roads under the power of my one body,"},{"time":35000,"text":"fuelled mostly by Twinkies and junk food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"And I've since then tried to keep technology"},{"time":41000,"text":"at arm's length in many ways, so it doesn't master my life."},{"time":45000,"text":"At the same time, I run a website on cool tools,"},{"time":49000,"text":"where I issue a daily obsession of the latest things in technology."},{"time":53000,"text":"So I'm still perplexed about what the true meaning of technology is"},{"time":59000,"text":"as it relates to humanity, as it relates to nature,"},{"time":63000,"text":"as it relates to the spiritual."},{"time":66000,"text":"And I'm not even sure we know what technology is."},{"time":70000,"text":"And one definition of technology is that which is first recorded."},{"time":76000,"text":"This is the first example of the modern use of technology that I can find."},{"time":81000,"text":"It was the suggested syllabus for dealing with"},{"time":85000,"text":"the Applied Arts and Science at Cambridge University in 1829."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"Before that, obviously, technology didn't exist. But obviously it did."},{"time":96000,"text":"I like one of the definitions that Alan Kay has for technology."},{"time":100000,"text":"He says technology is anything that was invented after you were born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":105000,"text":"So it sums up a lot of what we're talking about."},{"time":109000,"text":"Danny Hillis actually has an update on that --"},{"time":111000,"text":"he says technology is anything that doesn't quite work yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"Which also, I think, gets into a little bit of our current idea."},{"time":121000,"text":"But I was interested in another definition of technology."},{"time":124000,"text":"Something, again, that went back to something more fundamental."},{"time":128000,"text":"Something that was deeper. And as I struggled to understand that,"},{"time":134000,"text":"I came up with a way of framing the question"},{"time":137000,"text":"that seemed to work for me in my investigations."},{"time":139000,"text":"And I'm, this morning, going to talk about this for the first time."},{"time":142000,"text":"So this is a very rough attempt to think out loud."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"The question that I came up with was this question:"},{"time":151000,"text":"what does technology want? And by that, I don't mean,"},{"time":154000,"text":"does it want chocolate or vanilla? By what it wants, I mean,"},{"time":159000,"text":"what are its inherent trends and biases?"},{"time":161000,"text":"What are its tendencies over time? One way to think about this is"},{"time":166000,"text":"thinking about biological organisms, which we've heard a lot about."},{"time":170000,"text":"And the trick that Richard Dawkins does, which is to say,"},{"time":173000,"text":"to look at them as simply as genes, as vehicles for genes."},{"time":177000,"text":"So he's saying, what do genes want? The selfish gene."},{"time":180000,"text":"And I'm applying a similar trick to say,"},{"time":183000,"text":"what if we looked at the universe in our culture"},{"time":186000,"text":"through the eyes of technology? What does technology want?"},{"time":191000,"text":"Obviously, this in an incomplete question,"},{"time":193000,"text":"just as looking at an organism as only a gene"},{"time":195000,"text":"is an incomplete way of looking at it."},{"time":197000,"text":"But it's still very, very productive. So I'm attempting to say,"},{"time":201000,"text":"if we take technology's view of the world, what does it want?"},{"time":205000,"text":"And I think once we ask that question"},{"time":208000,"text":"we have to go back, actually, to life. Because obviously,"},{"time":213000,"text":"if we keep extending the origins of technology far back,"},{"time":216000,"text":"I think we come back to life at some point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"So that's where I want to begin my little exploration, is in life."},{"time":221000,"text":"And like you heard from the previous speakers,"},{"time":224000,"text":"we don't really know what life there is on Earth right now."},{"time":227000,"text":"We have really no idea."},{"time":229000,"text":"Craig Venter's tremendous and brilliant attempt"},{"time":233000,"text":"to DNA sequence things in the ocean is great."},{"time":236000,"text":"Brian Farrell's work is all part of this agenda to try"},{"time":239000,"text":"and actually discover all the species on Earth."},{"time":241000,"text":"And one of the things that we should do is just make a grid of the globe"},{"time":244000,"text":"and randomly go and inspect all the places that the grid intersects,"},{"time":249000,"text":"just to see what's on life. And if we did that"},{"time":251000,"text":"with our little Martian probe, which we have not done on Earth,"},{"time":254000,"text":"we would begin to see some incredible species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"This is not on another planet. These are things"},{"time":260000,"text":"that are hidden away on our planet."},{"time":262000,"text":"This is an ant that stores its colleagues' honey in its abdomen."},{"time":267000,"text":"Each one of these organisms that we've described -- that you've seen"},{"time":270000,"text":"from Jamie and others, these magnificent things --"},{"time":273000,"text":"what they're doing, each one of them,"},{"time":275000,"text":"is they're hacking the rules of life."},{"time":278000,"text":"I can't think of a single general principle of biology"},{"time":283000,"text":"that does not have an exception somewhere by some organism."},{"time":287000,"text":"Every single thing that we can think of --"},{"time":289000,"text":"and if you heard Olivia's talk about the sexual habits,"},{"time":292000,"text":"you'll realize that there isn't anything we can say that's true for all life,"},{"time":295000,"text":"because every single one of them is hacking something about it."},{"time":299000,"text":"This is a solar-powered sea slug. It's a nudibranch"},{"time":303000,"text":"that has incorporated chloroplast inside it to drive its energy."},{"time":309000,"text":"This is another version of that. This is a sea dragon,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and the one on the bottom, the blue one, is a juvenile that has not yet"},{"time":318000,"text":"swallowed the acid, has not yet taken in"},{"time":320000,"text":"the brown-green algae pond scum into its body to give it energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327000,"text":"These are hacks, and if we looked at the general shape"},{"time":332000,"text":"of the approaches to hacking life there are, current consensus,"},{"time":336000,"text":"six kingdoms. Six different broad approaches: the plants,"},{"time":340000,"text":"the animals, the fungi, the protests -- the little things -- the bacteria"},{"time":343000,"text":"and the Archaea bacteria. The Archaeas."},{"time":346000,"text":"Those are the general approaches to life. That's one way to look at life on Earth today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"But a more interesting way,"},{"time":354000,"text":"the current way to take the long view,"},{"time":357000,"text":"is to look at it in an evolutionary perspective."},{"time":360000,"text":"And here we have a view of evolution where rather than having evolution"},{"time":366000,"text":"go over the linear time, we have it coming out from the center."},{"time":369000,"text":"So in the center is the most primitive, and this is a genealogical chart"},{"time":373000,"text":"of all life on earth. This is all the same six kingdoms."},{"time":377000,"text":"You see 4,000 representative species, and you can see where we are."},{"time":381000,"text":"But what I like about this is it shows that"},{"time":382000,"text":"every living organism on Earth today is equally evolved."},{"time":388000,"text":"Those fungi and bacteria are as highly evolved as humans."},{"time":392000,"text":"They've been around just as long and gone through"},{"time":394000,"text":"just the same kind of trial and error to get here."},{"time":398000,"text":"But we see that each one of these is actually hacking,"},{"time":403000,"text":"and has a different way of finding out how to do life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"And if we take the long-term trends of life, if we begin to say,"},{"time":409000,"text":"what does evolution want? There's several things that we see."},{"time":412000,"text":"One of the things about evolution is that nowhere on Earth"},{"time":418000,"text":"have we ever been where we don't find life."},{"time":422000,"text":"We find life at the bottom of every long-term,"},{"time":426000,"text":"long-distance drilling core into the center of rock"},{"time":429000,"text":"that we bring up -- and there's bacteria in the pores of that rock."},{"time":433000,"text":"And wherever life is, it never retreats. It's ubiquitous and it wants to be more."},{"time":437000,"text":"More and more of the inert matter of the globe"},{"time":440000,"text":"is being touched and animated by life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443000,"text":"The second thing is is we see diversity. We also see specialization."},{"time":447000,"text":"We see the movement from a general-purpose cell"},{"time":450000,"text":"to the more specific and specialized."},{"time":454000,"text":"And we see a drift towards complexity that's very intuitive."},{"time":458000,"text":"And actually, we have current data that does show"},{"time":460000,"text":"that there is an actual drift towards complexity over time."},{"time":464000,"text":"And the last thing, I bring back this nudibranch."},{"time":466000,"text":"One of the things we see about life is that it moves"},{"time":469000,"text":"from the inner to increasing sociability. And by that it means"},{"time":473000,"text":"that there is more and more of life whose entire environment is other life."},{"time":477000,"text":"Like those chloroplast cells --"},{"time":479000,"text":"they're completely surrounded by other life."},{"time":480000,"text":"They never touch the inner matter. There is more and more co-evolution."},{"time":486000,"text":"And so the general, long-term trends of evolution"},{"time":489000,"text":"are roughly these five: ubiquity, diversity, specialization,"},{"time":493000,"text":"complexity and socialization. Now, I took that and said,"},{"time":498000,"text":"OK, what are the long-term trends in technology?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":503000,"text":"And again, my question is, what does technology want?"},{"time":507000,"text":"And so, remarkably, I discovered"},{"time":510000,"text":"that there's also a drift toward specialization."},{"time":513000,"text":"That we see there's a general hammer,"},{"time":516000,"text":"and hammers become more and more specific over time."},{"time":519000,"text":"There's obviously diversity. Huge numbers of things."},{"time":524000,"text":"This is all the contents of a Japanese home."},{"time":526000,"text":"I actually had my daughter -- gave her a tally counter,"},{"time":529000,"text":"and I gave her an assignment last summer to go around"},{"time":531000,"text":"and count the number of species of technology in our household."},{"time":535000,"text":"And it came up with 6,000 different species of products."},{"time":538000,"text":"I did some research and found out that the King of England, Henry VIII,"},{"time":541000,"text":"had only about 7,000 items in his household."},{"time":544000,"text":"And he was the King of England,"},{"time":545000,"text":"and that was the entire wealth of England at the time."},{"time":547000,"text":"So we're seeing huge numbers of diversity in the kinds of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"This is a scene from Star Wars where the 3PO comes out"},{"time":556000,"text":"and he sees machines making machines. How depraved!"},{"time":559000,"text":"Well, this is actually what we're headed towards: world machines."},{"time":563000,"text":"And the technology is only being thrown out by other technologies."},{"time":566000,"text":"Most machines will only ever be in contact with other technology"},{"time":569000,"text":"and not non-technology, or even life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"And thirdly, the idea that machines are becoming biological and complex"},{"time":575000,"text":"is at this point a cliche. And I'm happy to say,"},{"time":579000,"text":"I was partly responsible for that cliche"},{"time":581000,"text":"that machines are becoming biological, but that's pretty evident."},{"time":584000,"text":"So the major trends in technology evolution actually"},{"time":590000,"text":"are the same as in biological evolution. The same drives that we see"},{"time":595000,"text":"towards ubiquity, towards diversity, towards socialization,"},{"time":598000,"text":"towards complexity. That is maybe not a big surprise"},{"time":602000,"text":"because if we map out, say, the evolution of armor,"},{"time":607000,"text":"you can actually follow a sort of an evolutionary-type cladistic tree."},{"time":611000,"text":"I suggest that, in fact, technology is the seventh kingdom of life."},{"time":616000,"text":"That its operations and how it works is so similar"},{"time":620000,"text":"that we can think of it as the seventh kingdom."},{"time":624000,"text":"And so it would be sort of approximately up there,"},{"time":627000,"text":"coming out of the animal kingdom. And if we were to do that,"},{"time":633000,"text":"we would find out -- we could actually approach technology in this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"This is Niles Eldredge. He was the co-developer with Stephen Jay Gould"},{"time":641000,"text":"of the theory of punctuated equilibrium."},{"time":643000,"text":"But as a sideline, he happens to collect cornets."},{"time":646000,"text":"He has one of the world's largest collections -- about 500 of them."},{"time":650000,"text":"And he has decided to treat them as if they were trilobites, or snails,"},{"time":653000,"text":"and to do a morphological analysis,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and try to derive their genealogical history over time."},{"time":659000,"text":"This is his chart, which is not quite published yet."},{"time":661000,"text":"But the most interesting aspect about this"},{"time":664000,"text":"is that if you look at those red lines at the bottom,"},{"time":667000,"text":"those indicate basically a parentage of a type of cornet"},{"time":674000,"text":"that was no longer made. That does not happen in biology."},{"time":678000,"text":"When something is extinct, you can't have it as your parent."},{"time":681000,"text":"But that does happen in technology. And it turns out"},{"time":684000,"text":"that that's so distinctive that you can actually look at this tree,"},{"time":688000,"text":"and you can actually use it to determine"},{"time":691000,"text":"that this is a technological system versus a biological system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695000,"text":"In fact, this idea of resurrecting the whole idea is so important"},{"time":699000,"text":"that I began to think about what happens with old technology."},{"time":703000,"text":"And it turns out that, in fact, technologies don't die."},{"time":708000,"text":"So I suggested this to an historian of science, and he said,"},{"time":710000,"text":"\"Well, what about, you know, come on, what about steam cars?"},{"time":715000,"text":"They're not around anymore.\" Well actually, they are."},{"time":719000,"text":"In fact, they're so around that you can buy new parts for a Stanley steam automobile."},{"time":726000,"text":"And this is a website of a guy who's selling brand new parts"},{"time":729000,"text":"for the Stanley automobile. And the thing that I liked"},{"time":733000,"text":"is sort of this one-click, add-to-your-cart button --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"(Laughter) --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"for buying steam valves. I mean, it was just -- it was really there."},{"time":742000,"text":"And so, I began to think about, well, maybe that's just a random sample."},{"time":747000,"text":"Maybe I should do this sort of in a more conservative way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"So I took the great big 1895 Montgomery Ward's catalog"},{"time":755000,"text":"and I randomly went through it. And I took a page -- not quite a random page --"},{"time":758000,"text":"I took a page that was actually more difficult than others"},{"time":761000,"text":"because lots of the pages are filled with things"},{"time":763000,"text":"that are still being made. But I took this page"},{"time":766000,"text":"and I said, how many of these things are still being made?"},{"time":770000,"text":"And not antiques. I want to know how many of these things are still in production."},{"time":775000,"text":"And the answer is: all of them."},{"time":778000,"text":"All of them are still being produced. So you've got corn shellers."},{"time":785000,"text":"I don't know who needs a corn sheller."},{"time":787000,"text":"Be it corn shellers -- you've got ploughs; you've got fan mills;"},{"time":791000,"text":"all these things -- and these are not, again, antiques. These are --"},{"time":794000,"text":"you can order these. You can go to the web and you can buy them now,"},{"time":797000,"text":"brand-new made. So in a certain sense, technologies don't die."},{"time":802000,"text":"In fact, you can buy, for 50 bucks, a stone-age knife"},{"time":809000,"text":"made exactly the same way that they were made 10,000 years ago."},{"time":813000,"text":"It's short, bone handle, 50 bucks. And in fact,"},{"time":817000,"text":"what's important is that this information actually never died out."},{"time":820000,"text":"It's not just that it was resurrected. It's continued all along."},{"time":822000,"text":"And in Papua New Guinea, they were making stone axes"},{"time":825000,"text":"until two decades ago, just as a course of practical matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"Even when we try to get rid of a technology, it's actually very hard."},{"time":836000,"text":"So we've all heard about the Amish giving up cars."},{"time":840000,"text":"We've heard about the Japanese giving up guns."},{"time":842000,"text":"We've heard about this and that. But I actually went back and"},{"time":844000,"text":"took what I could find, the examples in history"},{"time":847000,"text":"where there have been prohibitions against technology,"},{"time":850000,"text":"and then I tried to find out when they came back in,"},{"time":853000,"text":"because they always came back in. And it turns out that the time,"},{"time":856000,"text":"the duration of when they were outlawed and prohibited,"},{"time":858000,"text":"is decreasing over time. And that basically, you can delay technology,"},{"time":863000,"text":"but you can't kill it. So this makes sense, because in a certain sense"},{"time":866000,"text":"what culture is, is the accumulation of ideas."},{"time":871000,"text":"That's what it's for. It's so that ideas don't die out."},{"time":874000,"text":"And when we take that, we take this idea of what culture is doing"},{"time":880000,"text":"and add it to what the long-term trajectory -- again, in life's evolution --"},{"time":886000,"text":"we find that each case -- each of the major transitions in life --"},{"time":889000,"text":"what they're really about is accelerating and changing"},{"time":892000,"text":"the way in which evolution happens."},{"time":895000,"text":"They're actually changing the way in which ideas are generated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898000,"text":"So all these steps in evolution are increasing, basically,"},{"time":902000,"text":"the evolution of evolvability."},{"time":904000,"text":"So what's happening over time in life is"},{"time":906000,"text":"that the ways in which you generate these new ideas, these new hacks,"},{"time":909000,"text":"are increasing. And the real tricks are ways"},{"time":913000,"text":"in which you kind of explore the way of exploring."},{"time":916000,"text":"And then what we see in the singularity,"},{"time":918000,"text":"that prophesized by Kurzweil and others --"},{"time":921000,"text":"his idea that technology is accelerating evolution."},{"time":925000,"text":"It's accelerating the way in which we search for ideas."},{"time":928000,"text":"So if you have life hacking --"},{"time":931000,"text":"life means hacking, the game of survival --"},{"time":933000,"text":"then evolution is a way to extend the game by changing the rules of the game."},{"time":937000,"text":"And what technology is really about is better ways to evolve."},{"time":941000,"text":"That is what we call an \"infinite game.\""},{"time":944000,"text":"That's the definition of \"infinite game.\" A finite game is play to win,"},{"time":947000,"text":"and an infinite game is played to keep playing."},{"time":950000,"text":"And I believe that technology is actually a cosmic force."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955000,"text":"The origins of technology was not in 1829,"},{"time":958000,"text":"but was actually at the beginning of the Big Bang,"},{"time":961000,"text":"and at that moment the entire huge billions of stars in the universe"},{"time":965000,"text":"were compressed. The entire universe was compressed into a little quantum dot,"},{"time":969000,"text":"and it was so tight in there, there was no room for any difference at all."},{"time":972000,"text":"That's the definition. There was no temperature."},{"time":974000,"text":"There was no difference whatsoever. And at the Big Bang,"},{"time":977000,"text":"what it expanded was the potential for difference."},{"time":980000,"text":"So as it expands and as things expand what we have"},{"time":983000,"text":"is the potential for differences, diversity, options, choices,"},{"time":988000,"text":"opportunities, possibilities and freedoms."},{"time":990000,"text":"Those are all basically the same thing."},{"time":992000,"text":"And those are the things that technology brings us."},{"time":996000,"text":"That's what technology is bringing us: choices, possibilities, freedoms."},{"time":1000000,"text":"That's what it's about. It's this expansion of room to make differences."},{"time":1004000,"text":"And so a hammer, when we grab a hammer, that's what we're grabbing."},{"time":1008000,"text":"And that's why we continue to grab technology --"},{"time":1011000,"text":"because we want those things. Those things are good."},{"time":1013000,"text":"Differences, freedom, choices, possibilities."},{"time":1017000,"text":"And each time we make a new opportunity place,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"we're allowing a platform to make new ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023000,"text":"And I think it's really important. Because if you can imagine"},{"time":1026000,"text":"Mozart before the technology of the piano was invented --"},{"time":1029000,"text":"what a loss to society there would be."},{"time":1031000,"text":"Imagine Van Gogh being born"},{"time":1033000,"text":"before the technologies of cheap oil paints."},{"time":1036000,"text":"Imagine Hitchcock before the technologies of film."},{"time":1040000,"text":"Somewhere, today, there are millions of young children being born"},{"time":1045000,"text":"whose technology of self-expression has not yet been invented."},{"time":1050000,"text":"We have a moral obligation to invent technology"},{"time":1053000,"text":"so that every person on the globe has the potential"},{"time":1055000,"text":"to realize their true difference."},{"time":1058000,"text":"We want a trillion zillion species of one individuals."},{"time":1061000,"text":"That's what technology really wants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064000,"text":"I'm going to skip through some of the objections"},{"time":1066000,"text":"because I don't have answers to why there's deforestation."},{"time":1070000,"text":"I don't have an answer to the fact that there seem to be"},{"time":1073000,"text":"bad technologies. I don't have an answer to"},{"time":1075000,"text":"how this impacts on our dignity, other than to suggest that"},{"time":1079000,"text":"maybe the seventh kingdom, because it's so close to what life is about,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"maybe we can bring it back and have it help us monitor life."},{"time":1088000,"text":"Maybe in some ways"},{"time":1090000,"text":"the fact that what we're trying to do with technology is find a good home for it."},{"time":1095000,"text":"It's a terrible thing to spray DDT on cotton fields,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"but it's a really good thing to use"},{"time":1100000,"text":"to eliminate millions of cases of death due to malaria in a small village."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1104000,"text":"Our humanity is actually defined by technology."},{"time":1107000,"text":"All the things that we think that we really like about humanity"},{"time":1110000,"text":"is being driven by technology. This is the infinite game."},{"time":1115000,"text":"That's what we're talking about."},{"time":1117000,"text":"You see, technology is a way to evolve the evolution."},{"time":1121000,"text":"It's a way to explore possibilities and opportunities and create more."},{"time":1127000,"text":"And it's actually a way of playing the game, of playing all the games."},{"time":1132000,"text":"That's what technology wants."},{"time":1134000,"text":"And so when I think about what technology wants,"},{"time":1137000,"text":"I think that it has to do with the fact that every person here -- and I really believe this --"},{"time":1142000,"text":"every person here has an assignment. And your assignment is"},{"time":1147000,"text":"to spend your life discovering what your assignment is."},{"time":1150000,"text":"That recursive nature is the infinite game."},{"time":1153000,"text":"And if you play that well, you'll have other people involved,"},{"time":1156000,"text":"so even that game extends and continues even when you're gone."},{"time":1160000,"text":"That is the infinite game. And what technology is"},{"time":1163000,"text":"is the medium in which we play that infinite game."},{"time":1166000,"text":"And so I think that we should embrace technology"},{"time":1169000,"text":"because it is an essential part of our journey"},{"time":1172000,"text":"in finding out who we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1174000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1176000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}